    {
      "id": "consumed-view-node-contract-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Contract Note",
      "position": {
        "x": 700,
        "y": -40
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 520,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Rules\n\n1. The consumer node keeps one stable runtime type.\n2. The source node is addressed explicitly as `/graph.node#node-id`.\n3. The consumed view is selected explicitly from the addressed node's exposed views.\n4. `sourcePayload` is the render selector.\n5. `consumerKind` or similar intent metadata may affect labeling, grouping, or badges, but must not become runtime render type.\n\n## View Roles\n\nSome view roles are semantically special and should be treated as such:\n\n- `icon-view` (`node.web.icon`) is the canonical icon surface.\n- `node-view` / `graph-view` are not valid substitutes for `icon-view`.\n\nWhen a consumer needs an icon and the addressed graph does not expose `icon-view`, it should use a deterministic fallback glyph and emit a diagnostic such as `MISSING_ICON_VIEW`.\n\n## Data Shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"authority\": \"consume-view\",\n  \"sourceRef\": \"/graph.node\",\n  \"sourceNodeId\": \"node-id\",\n  \"sourcePayload\": \"node.web.summary\",\n  \"consumerKind\": \"template\"\n}\n```\n\n## Forbidden Promotion\n\nThe following promotion is invalid:\n\n- semantic kind -> runtime node type\n\nFor example, if a consumer is classified as `template`, the node may present that as a badge or label, but the runtime renderer must still be the consumer node renderer.\n\n## Consequence\n\n`graph-reference` and `port` should not invent a new renderer from source metadata. They should render the selected source view through the same consumer surface.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "markdown",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "markdown",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/markdown.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "markdown"
      }
    }
